    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-10T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="852"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d852">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">919.537/8–851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Panama</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-10T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 10, 1951—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> appreciates efforts Pan Govt cooperate
                    with <gloss target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss> Res May 18 concerning embargo on war
                    materials to areas under control Chi Communists and North Koreans re <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 107 Aug 6<note n="1" xml:id="d852fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> and 116 Aug 8.<note n="1" xml:id="d852fn2">Not
                        printed.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> believes Pan Govt as result <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> actions fully aware views this Govt on
                    importance this issue and on need for effective measures. <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> has been hopeful Pan Govt could find way to
                    take action in line Alfaro views <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 95 Aug
                        3.<note n="1" xml:id="d852fn3">Not printed.</note> Apart from uncertain
                    legal basis for action which cannot be fully appraised here <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> considers decision whether Pan Govt has
                    authority to issue decree or must seek further authority from Natl Assembly is
                    of course a matter which Pan officials must determine for themselves. In latter
                    event, Pan Govt might consider it desirable continue meanwhile handling shipping
                    controls on present individual basis until appropriate legal authority
                    obtained.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> believes <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                        >Emb</gloss> shld avoid action beyond informally stressing our objectives
                    and shld not be in position urging specific terms of decree.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
